Key Functions:
Write:

java.nio.file: Files.writeString(path, content), Files.write(path, data)
java.io: FileWriter, BufferedWriter, PrintWriter
Read:

java.nio.file: Files.readString(path), Files.readAllLines(path)
java.io: FileReader, BufferedReader, InputStreamReader
Summary:
NIO = More flexible and efficient for modern Java applications.
IO = Simpler and sufficient for basic tasks or compatibility.